  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The following code returns 1 instead of 0 because the addition overflows. The assembly code shows that the AND mask is applied before the addition and not after, resulting in the corruption of b.\n\n```\ncontract Test {\n    uint32 a = 0xFFFFFFFF;\n    uint32 b;\n\n    function run() returns (uint32) {\n        var x = 1;\n        a = uint32(a + x);\n        return b;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nI suppose that writing in a should not corrupt b in any case.\n\nSolidity version: 0.4.3+commit.2353da71.Emscripten.clang\n",
